data.title: Payee Disclosure Reports Â« Crown Investments Corporation of Saskatchewan
data.text:
CIC Crown corporations and related agencies are required to publicly disclose payee information to the Standing Committee on Crown and Central Agencies on an annual basis. The report lists payments from April 1 - March 31 each year in the areas of:

suppliers and other payments;

grants, contributions, donations and sponsorships;

ministerial expenses;

board expenses; and

remuneration.
